With some minor tweaks, I ran this script and examined the cloud-output.log. I saw pretty normal looking responses. When a create operation was in progress, I would get this response to another request;
{"CloudFormationErrorResponse" : {"RequestId":"e93ef4be-235a-44a9-bc16-10fd79889d4c","Error":[{"Type":"Sender","Code":"StackOperationInProgress","Message":"A stack operation is ongoing (CREATE_IN_PROGRESS), please try again later.","Detail":{}}]}}

The main tweak to the script was this line;
tester = boto.connect_cloudformation(region=region, port=8773, path="/services/CloudFormation", is_secure=False,
The others were for keys and ids that existed on my cloud/account.
